      <title>Interesting Facts About Panic Disorders</title>
      <link>http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/interesting-facts-about-panic-disorders/</link>
      <comments>http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/interesting-facts-about-panic-disorders/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 04 Jul 2011 15:27:29 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>panicattacks</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Overcoming Panic Attacks]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[panic attacks facts]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[panic puzzle]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/?p=1070</guid>
      <description>Panic Disorders Facts When panic attacks occur, it causes the sufferer to actually lose their sense of reality. They will actually appear to be hyperventilating and the fear is really genuine. To Read About a Recommended Program For Overcoming Panic Attacks Click Here As stated they could appear to be frightened and lost amid their [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/overcoming-panic-attacks/Overcoming_Panic_Attacks-Interesting_Facts_About_Panic_Disorders.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1>Panic Disorders Facts</h1>
<p>When panic attacks occur, it causes the sufferer to actually lose their sense of reality. They will actually appear to be hyperventilating and the fear is really genuine.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><em><em><em><em><em><em><em><em>To Read About a Recommended Program <a href="http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/thelindenmethod">For Overcoming Panic Attacks Click Here</a></em></em></em></em></em></em></em></em></h3>
<p>As stated they could appear to be frightened and lost amid their surroundings. The physical manifestations will appear as excessive sweating and a rapid increase in the breathing.</p>
<p>Here are  some very interesting facts about this frightening disorder:</p>
<p>1) The attack can happen at any time and anywhere and this is frightening in itself. The body will not give any warning signs that it is starting or will occur.</p>
<p>2) A panic attack can last anywhere from 20 seconds to a couple of hours, but it will end. As each patient is unique and the circumstances that cause the attacks are also unique, then it follows that the attacks will be unique in themselves. Also the signs and symptoms will also vary.</p>
<p>However reading this fact will not lessen the actual fear which is felt by the sufferer of the <a href="http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com">panic attack</a>.</p>
<p>3) You have to remember that panic attacks will not kill you, because the cause is not physical. However symptoms such as an increase in your heart beat needs to be checked out by your doctor to ensure that there is not another serious problem which has not been diagnosed.</p>
<p>4) The most effective treatments for panic disorders and anxiety that accompany them is actually identifying the causes of the problem. Thus by identifying the triggers, you can instigate a program whereby you can avoid these triggers or circumstances which cause the attacks.</p>
<p>5) You do not need to take prescribed medicines in order to prevent or stop the panic attacks and the stress and anxiety which the patient feels. In addition please remember that you do not need to invest hundreds or even thousands of dollars for a cure.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><em><em><em><em>To Read About a Recommended Program For <a href="../panicpuzzle">Overcoming Panic Attacks Click Here</a></em></em></em></em></h3>
<p>The problem is actually far more common than people realise and above all it&#8217;s important to realise and remember that many have found the treatment that has helped  them in overcoming panic attacks.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
