      <category><![CDATA[controlling panic attacks]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[how to deal with panic attacks]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[panic attacks while pregnant]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/?p=222</guid>
      <description>Panic Attacks During Pregnancy photo credit: gatis.orlickisFor many women, it’s not uncommon to experience panic attacks during pregnancy. Even if you were never diagnosed with any mood disorders while you were in your teens. There’s a 90% chance that you’ll experience frequent panic attacks while you’re carrying your child. This is because of the hormonal [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/overcoming-panic-attacks/Overcoming_Panic_Attacks-Panic_Attacks_During__Pregnancy.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1>Panic Attacks During  Pregnancy</h1>
<p><!-- 		@page { size: 21cm 29.7cm; margin: 2cm } 		P { margin-bottom: 0.21cm } --></p>
<div class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 170px"><a title="Awaiting" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/23023192@N02/3646054481/" target="_blank"><img style="border: 0pt none;" title="Panic Attacks During Pregnancy" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3398/3646054481_9af4a7fd51_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Panic Attacks During Pregnancy" width="160" height="240" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Panic Attacks During Pregnancy</p></div>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="gatis.orlickis" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/23023192@N02/3646054481/" target="_blank">gatis.orlickis</a></small>For many women, it’s not uncommon to experience <strong>panic attacks during pregnancy</strong>. Even if you were never diagnosed with any mood disorders while you were in your teens.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">There’s a 90% chance that you’ll experience frequent panic attacks while you’re carrying your child.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">This is because of the hormonal changes that your pregnant body is going through. Aside from the biological causes, women also feel temporary bouts of anxiety about their body’s changes, and the thought of giving birth to a child.</p>
<p>If  you’ve experienced waking up in the middle of the night with your heart  racing, your entire body br</p>
<p>eaking out into a cold sweat, and unable to  go back to sleep several times in a week, you’re most likely suffering  from panic attacks at night.  According  to studies, most sleeping disorders are actually connected to panic or  anxiety disorders.</p>
<p>While older people might just brush this off as a  case of “bad dreams”, medical experts find that these panic attacks are  actually biologically influenced.</p>
<p>Anxiety disorders or clinical depression, which cause <a href="http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com">panic attacks</a> at night,  are in turn caused by chemical balances in the brain. When treated  early, this can be cured though cognitive psychotherapy, or in layman’s  terms, counseling.</p>
<p>While  panic attacks are commonly linked to mood disorders, this connection is  not reason enough for you to jump right into taking antidepressants and  mood stabilizers. Chemical mood medications have a lot of side effects,  and they can be highly addictive as well.</p>
<p>You  might want to do away with your medication one day only to find out that  you can’t do so abruptly without suffering from withdrawal symptoms.  This is the reason why a lot of people are looking for <a href="http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/the-linden-method-is-it-a-scam/">natural treatment for panic attacks.</a></p>
<p>If you’ve caught this during the latter, more severe  cases, however, you may be asked to take antidepressants and/or mood  stabilizers under the care of your doctor.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">If you’re pregnant and you wish to get rid of these panic attacks, it’s absolutely out of the question to take medications because it can harm you and your child.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><em><em>To Read About a Recommended Program For <a href="../thelindenmethod">Overcoming Panic Attacks Click Here</a></em></em></h3>
<p>However, panic attacks during pregnancy aren’t good either because it  can cause premature deliveries. To make sure that you carry your child  full term, you should contact a mental health specialist right away to  ask about the possibilities of a cognitive psychotherapy.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
