      <title>Panic Attacks Symptoms – What Are They.</title>
      <link>http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/symptoms-panic-attacks/</link>
      <comments>http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/symptoms-panic-attacks/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 10 Feb 2010 15:53:10 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>panicattacks</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Overcoming Panic Attacks]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[overcome panic attacks]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[panic puzzle]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[symptoms of panic attacks]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com/?p=19</guid>
      <description>Panic Attacks Symptoms Some people hold back on treatment because they don’t really know what panic attacks symptoms are. They think the just have “stage fright” because they’ve been experiencing it all their lives. As an example, other people  think that they’re just not born to drive, when in fact, the heart racing incidents during [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/overcoming-panic-attacks/Overcoming_Panic_Attacks-Panic_Attacks_Symptoms__What_Are_They.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h1>Panic Attacks Symptoms</h1>
<p>Some people hold back on treatment because they don’t really know what <strong>panic attacks symptoms </strong>are.   They think the just have “stage fright” because they’ve been   experiencing it all their lives.</p>
<p>As an example, other people  think that they’re just not   born to drive, when in fact, the heart racing incidents during their   driving lessons were already give away signs or symptoms of panic attack.</p>
<h2>Panic Attack Symptoms &#8211; A List Of Symptoms</h2>
<p>The panic attacks symptoms can be frightening and can suddenly come unaware to the sufferers. They can range from:</p>
<ul>
<li>Chest pain, rapid heart beat or palpitations. It must be stressed that these type of symptoms should be checked out by a doctor. Have yourself a checkup.</li>
<li>Shaking visibly which can be very worrying to a partner or friend.</li>
<li>Feeling unsteady or feeling dizzy</li>
<li>Feeling nausea or having  indigestion</li>
<li>You have a fear that you are going crazy or have lost control.</li>
<li>Feeling numb or have tingling sensations in the areas of the face or body. Again this needs to be checked out by a doctor.</li>
<li>Have  hot flushes.</li>
<li>Blushing or skin blotches</li>
<li>Urgent need to go to the toilet</li>
<li>Pain in the neck and shoulders</li>
</ul>
<p>Perhaps,  it’s even inaccurate to call them <a href="http://www.overcomingpanicattackstoday.com">symptoms of panic attacks</a> because  panic attack in itself is already a symptom of one of the most common  mood disorders. If you’ve been having trouble sleeping because you wake  up having difficulty breathing, it’s quite possible that you’re showing  signs of mild OCD, depression, and/or other anxiety disorders.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><em><em>To Read About a Recommended Program For <a href="../thelindenmethod">Overcoming Panic Attacks Click Here</a></em></em></h3>
<p>When you  have frequent and unexplainable panic attacks, and if it have put your  life or your job on the line many times, you should consult a mental  health specialist right away. These mood disorders could be serious, but  when they’re spotted early, they can be treated without medication.</p>
<p>If  you’re suffering from constant panic attacks, and you’re not doing  anything about it, it’s most likely that you lack enough knowledge about  the disorder you’re going through.</p>
<h3>Panic Attack Symptoms &#8211; Understanding Them</h3>
<p>It is  necessary if you want to pull the problem from the roots. Panic attacks  can take over your career, and it can put the life of others and  yourself if you’re not careful.</p>
<p>The fact  is that panic attacks are usually symptoms or signs of bigger mood  disorders. There’s always a huge possibility that you’re clinically  depressed or suffering form OCD when you experience panic attacks. The  longer you let these disorders go untreated, the more severe they  become. You should consult a mental health specialist as soon as your  first spells of panic attacks.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s important to identify the causes or <em>panic attacks symptoms</em> in order that you can make a proper decision on the correct treatment. Then you can have a better quality of life and enjoy it to the full.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
